<div class="container">

  <div class="jumbotron text-center">
      <h1>simple file upload</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-sm-offset-0">

          <form action="/upload" method="POST" encType="multipart/form-data">
            <div class="form-group">
              <h3>User Stories:</h3>
              <li>I can submit a form object that includes a file upload.
              <li>The from file input field has the "name" attribute set to "upfile". We rely on this in testing.
              <li>When I submit something, I will receive the file name, and size in bytes within the JSON response.
             <br><br>

             <label for="file" class ="control-label col-sm-2">Select file:</label>
             <input type="file" id="upfile" name="upfile" class ="control-label col-sm-5" accept="" required="" >
             <div class ="control-label col-sm-4">
              <button type="submit" name="submit" class="btn btn-success">Submit</button>
             </div>
            </div>
        	</form>

     </div>
  </div>
</div>
